  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. It&rsquo;s given that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"p equals, 3 x plus 4 \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"v equals, x plus 5\"></span>. Substituting the values for <span class=\"italic\">p</span> and <span class=\"italic\">v</span> into the expression <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"p v, minus 2 p, plus v \"></span> yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, 3 x plus 4, close parenthesis, times, open parenthesis, x plus 5, close parenthesis, minus, 2 times, open parenthesis, 3 x plus 4, close parenthesis, plus x, plus 5\"></span>. Multiplying the terms <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, 3 x plus 4, close parenthesis, times, open parenthesis, x plus 5, close parenthesis\"></span> yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 x squared, plus 4 x, plus 15 x, plus 20\"></span>. Using the distributive property to rewrite <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 2 times, open parenthesis, 3 x plus 4, close parenthesis\"></span> yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 6 x minus 8\"></span>. Therefore, the entire expression can be represented as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 x squared, plus 4 x, plus 15 x, plus 20, minus 6 x, minus 8, plus x, plus 5\"></span>. Combining like terms yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 x squared, plus 14 x, plus 17\"></span>.<p>Choice A is incorrect and may result from subtracting, instead of adding, the term <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x plus 5\"></span>. Choice C is incorrect. This is the result of multiplying the terms <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, 3 x plus 4, close parenthesis, times, open parenthesis, x plus 5, close parenthesis\"></span>. Choice D is incorrect and may result from distributing 2, instead of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 2\"></span>, to the term <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 x plus 4\"></span>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
